BINTULU: Universiti Putra Malaysia Bintulu Campus (UPMKB) agriculture and livestock researchers have been asked to use their expertise to help local farmers increase their yields.Chancellor Sultan Sharafuddin Idris Shah said that it is necessary for the university to expand cooperation with various parties, especially those involved in agriculture and livestock activities.“I was informed that the agriculture and deep sea fishing sectors are also emphasised in the implementation of the Sarawak Corridor of Renewable Energy (SCORE).“Thus the establishment of university campus here is timely since this area is having vast industrial development,” he said during a dinner on Monday.He praised the university for being very influential in helping to produce more experts in various fields to support SCORE’s development.